 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Tools Development Engineer Hewlett Packard Enterprise 4,796 reviews Durham, NC Hewlett Packard Enterprise 4,796 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job Company Job details Salary $122,500 - $177,500 a year Full Job Description Senior Tools Development Engineer 
Design and develop tools for internal engineering teams including test automation frameworks, automated infrastructure deployment tools, storage load generation / data integrity test tools, build and release automation, and similar. The primary development environment is Python, with other languages and tools as appropriate. 
Responsibilities: 
Collect requirements, design and develop new tools for internal engineering customers. 
Design robust automation framework for running, managing, and reporting unit and functional tests. 
Maintain existing tools & infrastructure. 
Analyze, design, and develop new features based on the customers’ requirements. 
Evolve our continuous integration (CI) pipelines function in support of one or more of the products. 
Learn newer technologies and enhance existing system to be robust and efficient. 
Work in an agile development environment to organize and deliver working software in predictable iterations. 
Collaborate with Development, Release, Support, and QA Engineers to build efficient infrastructure, tools, and automation frameworks. 
About You: 
This position requires a self-driven individual with very strong technical and communication skills who can collaborate in a distributed team environment. 
A proficient and skilled software developer with a deep knowledge of Python and a front-end framework such as Angular or React. 
Solid understanding of Cloud Infrastructure, IaaS, & SaaS platforms, Git, Jenkins, Docker. 
Experience using databases such as MySQL. 
Experience with Elastic Search and NoSQL databases such as CouchDB and MongoDB. 
Passionate in the area of infrastructure and tools development. 
Strong logical, analytical and problem-solving skills. 
Self-motivated and able to deliver on tight schedules with minimal supervision. 
Excellent written and verbal communication skills. 
Able to guide and mentor less-experienced team members. 
Education and Experience Required: 
Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, equivalent work experience. 
7+ years of experience at least in one of the following programming languages: Python, Perl, C, C++ 
Additional Preferred Knowledge and Skills: 
Strong Linux skills. 
VMware experience. 
REST API development experience. 
Understanding of CI/CD workflows. 
Knowledge of Ansible is a plus. 
Experience with PXE is a plus. 
Experience with Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning models, ML infrastructure, Natural Language Processing or Deep Learning – is a plus. 
HPE is an Equal Employment Opportunity/ Veterans/Disabled/LGBT and Affirmative Action employer. We are committed to diversity and building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We do not discriminate and all decisions we make are made on the basis of qualifications, merit, and business need. Our goal is to be one global diverse team that is representative of our customers, in an inclusive environment where we can continue to innovate and grow together. 
COLORADO ONLY: 
